values:
This was one fucked up weekend.&nbsp; Im&nbsp; decided Amber and i are just friends.&nbsp;&nbsp;If shes&nbsp;wanting more&nbsp; balls in her court but i doubt it.
I went to the virgin festival both saturday and sunday. Saturday i went with&nbsp; amber and melissa and had a decent time. buck 65 signed our ball which i got to kep and i Caught zig zags from Illscarlet which i got signed too. melissa got the tip of her penis lighter singed by them as well.&nbsp; 
Sunday i went alone and had a better time though.&nbsp;I&nbsp;just met people there.&nbsp;The strokes were actually really fun. probably the most fun band of the weekend. wolfmother was pretty awesome too. i liked there music best.&nbsp; the raconteurs were fun...though i didnt get to see them. i could hear them from where i was though. (lol, sue ellen ) I didnt get to listen to&nbsp; broken social scene&nbsp; because i was off checking out the moony suzuki and trying pursuade the security to let me back over a bridge so i could find my necklace. It was right where i thought it had fallen off so it took me 2 seconds when i could finally go which was unfortunally after the concert had ended.&nbsp; I wish massive attack had played though

Serious, sometimes my life is just WTF?&nbsp; I dont even know how i end up where i do.&nbsp;


PS. hahahahahahahahahahahahahahhaah
HAHAHAH. gonna be an awesome story.

I went to work today and found out i have 0 students booked. Ross&nbsp;has returned so he took them all back. It was good to see him again though. it looks like i wont have work for at least another week but most likely 2.&nbsp;

So I went home, put a few step function cds in my backpack, got on my bike, and pulled a ryans job today ( i made myself a whisky and OJ waterbottle hence the no driving). I only went to the pizza pizza, the grocery store, and the gas station and managed to sell 3 Cds. I was amazed how easy it was. Im thinking of heading to some high schools this week.

on a side note daft punk has some awesome tunes. I want to make some stuff like that now.

"And thats the end of frosty."

Phil left today for good to kentucky. Last night was our send off for him and the last time we'd see him. Jamies going to be pissed that he missed it but we tried calling him and julian even tried calling lish so there was nothing we could do.I still cant believe he's actually gone for good. Its goona be pretty weird hanging out with everyone and only he's missing.

yesterday was totally an end of a movie moment. lol, frosty was walking up the stairs to head out and i was at the top andn he was walking in slow motion so we could narrate while no excuses by alice in chains was playing: "...&nbsp;and thats the last we ever saw of andrew...." it was jokes, but actually like it.&nbsp;

have you ever thought of your life&nbsp;like seasons of a tv show about your life? Like for me i&nbsp;remember SEASON 7: York University.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; as an example&nbsp;

anyways,&nbsp;this would be a season finale episode. i guess now its time to be excited about the next season.&nbsp;






I should actually go through my life and figure out what season im in. I'll post&nbsp;teh list here.
*it doesnt go by birthdays, it goes by big events either emotionaly or ones that&nbsp; change things into a new stage of life
